/c/atlas-elektronik-gmbh/22289599', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/atlas-north-america-llc/346681852', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/caja-de-seguro-social/455482072', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/heatherwood-golf-club/46681078', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/heinrich-kopp-gmbh/372789517', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/medic-rescue/47367866', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/michigan-surgical-center-llc/90769926', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/shamrock-capital-advisors-llc/80380310', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/shamrock-holdings-inc/102187761', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/techmar-inc/37699777', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/thyssenkrupp-marine-systems/559786010', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/uniview-technologies-co-ltd/88113211']}}, {'title': 'WatchGuard: 45 CVEs, avg CVSS 8.04. 2 exploited in wild. 100% unpatched. Trust Score: D. Firebox & UTM users at risk. Fix your firewalls now. #WatchGuard #cybersecurity #infosechttps://www.valtersit.com/vendors/watchguard/', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 06 Jul 2026 00:48:01 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@hugovalters/116870097217674734', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['valtersit.com'], 'email-addr': ['hugovalters@mastodon.social'], 'url': ['http://www.valtersit.com']}}, {'title': "CVE-2026-59509 (CRITICAL): cve-search POST /fetch_cve_data allows unauth'd access to arbitrary MongoDB collections, exposing admin creds for offline cracking. Restrict endpoint, monitor activity, check vendor updates. https://radar.offseq.com/threat/ghsa-3fmp-59v6-4qw2-ddbb46f84ba1bbe2 #OffSeq #infosec #CVE202659509", 'publication_date': 'Mon, 06 Jul 2026 00:48:01 +0000', 'source': 'https://infosec.exchange/@offseq/116870089136632895', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["CVE-2026-59509 (CRITICAL): cve-search POST /fetch_cve_data allows unauth'd access to arbitrary MongoDB collections, exposing admin creds for offline cracking. Restrict endpoint, monitor activity, check vendor updates.https://radar.offseq.com/threat/ghsa-3fmp-59v6-4qw2-ddbb46f84ba1bbe2#OffSeq#infosec#CVE202659509"], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['radar.offseq.com'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-59509']}}, {'title': "Note to conference organizers: please do not wait until the last second to send out presentation acceptance/rejection letters. Some people require multiple month heads up (like me).I HOPE (ha!) that they can be better organized next year. Otherwise, I don't think I'll ever submit to HOPE again.#infosec #FreeBSD #HOPEConference #libhijack", 'publication_date': 'Sun, 05 Jul 2026 23:48:29 +0000', 'source': 'https://bsd.network/@lattera/116870022152389634', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'email-addr': ['lattera@bsd.network']}}, {'title': "CVE-2026-9085 - DNS Hijacking in TUBITAK BILGEM's Pardus-Parental-Control", 'publication_date': 'Sun, 05 Jul 2026 15:16:57 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-9085', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Incorrect Permission Assignment for Critical Resource, Improper Access Control vulnerability in TUBITAK BILGEM Software Technologies Research Institute Pardus-Parental-Control allows DNS Spoofing. This issue affects Pardus-Parental-Control: from <=0.5.1 before 0.7.0.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-9085vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-9085weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'email-addr': ['hey@cvefeed.io', 'iletisim@usom.gov.tr'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-9085']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-59509 - Unauthenticated arbitrary MongoDB collection read in cve-search', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 05 Jul 2026 13:16:56 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-59509', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['An unauthenticated improper input validation vulnerability in the POST /fetch_cve_data endpoint in cve-search. A remote attacker can manipulate request parameters controlling the MongoDB collection, projected fields, and regular-expression filters to read arbitrary application MongoDB collections. This can expose administrative usernames and password hashes from the mgmt_users collection, enabling offline password cracking and potential administrative account compromise.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-59509vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-59509weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'email-addr': ['hey@cvefeed.io'], 'url': ['https://github.com/cve-search/cve-search/', 'https://github.com/cve-search/cve-search/issues/1217', 'https://github.com/cve-search/cve-search/pull/1218'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-59509']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-14721 - UTT HiPER 1250GW Web Endpoint ConfigWirelessBase_5g stack-based overflow', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 05 Jul 2026 08:16:26 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-14721', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['A vulnerability has been found in UTT HiPER 1250GW up to 3.2.7-210907-180535. This affects an unknown function of the file /goform/ConfigWirelessBase_5g of the component Web Endpoint. The manipulation of the argument ssid leads to stack-based buffer overflow. The attack is possible to be carried out remotely. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-14721vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-14721weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['cna@vuldb.com'], 'url': ['https://github.com/J-CLOWN-TAROT/UTT', 'https://vuldb.com/cve/CVE-2026-14721', 'https://vuldb.com/submit/847632', 'https://vuldb.com/vuln/376308', 'https://vuldb.com/vuln/376308/cti'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-14721']}}, {'title': '三重県 庁のUSB メモリーから相次いで